    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-09-04T17:56:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-09-04T17:56:00-05:00" n="122"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d122">
                <head>122. Telegram 149761 From the Department of State to the Embassy in
                        Brazil<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d122fn1">Source: National Archives,
                        RG 59, Central Files 1967–69, <gloss target="#POL1">POL</gloss> 23–9 BRAZ.
                        Secret; Exdis; Flash. Drafted by Dean; cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MCA1">Meyer</persName> and Executive Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_ETL1">Eliot</persName>; and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_RE1">Richardson</persName>.</note>
                    <note n="2" type="summary" xml:id="d122fn2">Under Secretary Richardson stated
                        that the U.S. Government should comply with the demands of the kidnappers to
                        secure Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_ECB1">Elbrick</persName>’s
                        release.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1969-09-04T22:56:00+00:00">September 4, 1969, 2256Z</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <pb facs="d122-1" n="1" xml:id="pg_d122-1"/>
                <list type="references">
                    <head>Reference:</head>
                    <item>Belton/Dean Telcon</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>Subject:</head>
                    <item>Kidnapping of Ambassador</item>
                </list>
                <p>1. Concerning demands contained in kidnapper’s note, our position vis-a-vis
                        <gloss target="#GOB1">GOB</gloss> should be that safe return of Amb Elbrick
                    is of over-riding importance to us and we urge that all measures be taken,
                    including compliance with kidnapper’s demands if necessary. Should it appear
                    that any GOB strategy concerning the search is carrying them dangerously close
                    to the 48-hour deadline without locating the Ambassador, you should reiterate
                    forcefully our desire for GOB compliance with kidnappers’ demands.</p>
            </div>
